cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.AI. 

The paper is about personalized search in e-commerce, which involves information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of query-item features and session features, which are related to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), making cs.CL a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of logistic regression, gradient boosted decision trees, rank svm, and a novel deep match model, which are all ML techniques, making cs.CE and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well.
